Ask HN: What's your experience in the “twilight zone” of middle-market cloud?
text:
When you're getting started, the onramp and DevEx of Platform-as-a-services such as Vercel, Heroku, App Engine and Fly.io are compelling.

Eventually, the cost structure means your team has to reach for infrastructure-as-a-service providers such as AWS, Azure, and GCP.

I'm presuming most teams move from PaaS -> IaaS more frequently than the other way around. Did you do a direct migration or is there some middleground cloud provider such as DigitalOcean?

Is this an interim buffer area where you quickly try to move to IaaS, or has your team lingered halfway between IaaS and PaaS?

Ask HN: Fastest way to stop potential Google Wallet phishing campaign?
text: Yesterday I got a spam mail in German claiming a new sign-in to my Google Wallet Account from a OnePlus 5 device. It contains a link to https://googlewallet-support.com/pay/0000000a00000 (real id redacted), which I guess is some personalized URL and therefore I didn't open it. Opening the URL with an invalid id just redirects to google.nl. I tried to report the domain with the registrar (NameSilo) but got an answer that they couldn't verify that it's used for phishing. I reported the domain with Google Safe Browsing but so far it's not being recognized as malicious by Chromium or Firefox. What else can I do?
